scene.message:
Maki: Ms. Saeko is always so{nl}
gloomy! It starts to bring{nl}
me down too.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Ms. Saeko's gotta have{nl}
that energy of hers, or it{nl}
throws me right off.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: If Mayuzumi saw Ms.{nl}
Saeko as she is now, she'd{nl}
be terribly disappointed.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Wha- huh?{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Hey, what's up, Ms. Saeko?{waitkey}If you tell me again it's{nl}
just 'cause I overate and{nl}
feel sick, I'll get mad!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: At least she's not{nl}
making me do push-ups as{nl}
punishment — maybe this is{nl}
better.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: For that Ms. Saeko to{nl}
stay silent...{wait_fr:32} Could she be{nl}
terribly angry about{nl}
something?{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Even with the same{nl}
face, a different temperament{nl}
changes the whole air about{nl}
a person, doesn't it.{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:32}Hmph. At least{nl}
she's not noisy. That's{nl}
something.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: Oh, {ctl0f:1}.{nl}
Did you hurt yourself{nl}
somewhere?{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Ah, Ms. Saeko! Hey{nl}
there, long time no see!{nl}
My, as lovely as ever...{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Ah, it's Ms. Saeko!{nl}
Teacher, it's Ayase. You{nl}
recognize me?{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Oh my, Ms. Saeko. About{nl}
earlier, our apologies for{nl}
the trouble...{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: That gave me{nl}
such a fright earlier!{waitkey}But I hear you all came to{nl}
the rescue. Thank you so much!{waitkey}{ret}

Agastya Tree:{nl}
Shall I inscribe{nl}
your record within me?{waitkey}{nl}
{ctl0e:0}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: When you're{nl}
feeling unwell, come to the{nl}
infirmary. Now, let me have{nl}
a look at you.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: There, all done.{nl}
Don't go losing to any{nl}
demons, now.{waitkey}{ret}
